2.00	Thirunamam	Thirunamam	Thirunamam Thiru (word representing sacredness) + Namam (name), --&gt; The Sacred name. It represents the 'Sacred name of God'. The phrase Namam also represents the coarse white soil found at the deeper layer of earth, which is used as the powder to wear a flame shaped mark. The Ayyavazhi people wore this Namam, starting from the central point between the eyebrows, going straight up near the top edge of the forehead.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/aa/Brownring-Lotus.png/150px-Brownring-Lotus.png
